I had been to Pakistan,Lahore,Sheikopura Karachi, Peshawar,Rawalpindi,on business visas,Muree & Burban hill stations my personal  experience is that most of the effluent well educated persons are too good,very hospitable people,one to one they are very courteous & hospitable human beings.
They love to come to India,& do their shopping shopping every time they have visited.
I think it's their politians & army rulers,who do not want to have a congenial atmosphere between the two countries' because of their own survival.
Else Indian Companies have been doing a roaring business in exporting good to Pakistan.😊Ultimately they are at a very big loss,as they have to import from Europe or China.😢
